We've made it our business to craft perfectly burning candles. We believe that your candle should not look pretty and smell good, but they should also WORK! This is why Jill Rosenwald trusts us to craft candles for her extremely successful pottery brand.

Our partnership started in the early days of the pandemic when @jillrosenwald was looking for a way to drive more traffic to her ecommerce site. We knew the candles would be a hit for her customers but neither of us had any idea just how far this would go. Fast forward 3 years and we have made over 1,000 candles in these gorgeous vessels. Jill's customers love them and so do we!

❤️HELLO❤️EVERYONE❤️Allow me to re-introduce myself here on Instagram. My name is Jill Rosenwald. My husband Lawrence McRae and I run a hopping pottery studio in the Seaport in Boston. Two weeks ago my Instagram account got hacked by a Crypto currency hawker. Some of you may have thought it was me selling crypto currency and boasting about my new fancy new car, but I assure you IT WAS NOT. I am simple that way. I just talk about pottery and design and sh*t I like over here. Thank you to everyone who reached out to me with their support and help. I am so grateful to be back on the platform❤️💗❤️

🔥WAREHOUSE SALE🔥DROPS TOMORROW🔥at 10 am EST. Here are some FAQ’s
Q. Is the sale in person?
A. No, it will be online.
Q. How do I access?
A. I will put the link in my bio & in my story at 10am EST.
Q. How many pieces are in the sale?
A. About 150.
Q. Can I hold things in my cart?
A. No. Things that linger in a cart remain available to others.
Q. How quickly do things sell?
A. I am never sure but in the past we have sold pieces well.
Q. Is this a SALE?
A. Some pieces are aggressively marked down others mildly and some new pieces are full price. It’s a melange!
Q. How quickly will you ship because I know things take a while?
A. All these pieces are in stock and ready to ship!
Q. If I am local, May I come by the studio to grab my purchase?
A. YES! Just choose “pickup” at check out and you’ll access FREE shipping.
Q. I think I spy a Lawrence McRae piece in the sneak peeks! Will his pieces be in the sale?
A. YES! We do have a small selection of his pieces in the Sale.

For years we had a board in our studio we called the “chip wall” where we hung all our little color tile samples. It was a workers tool not really meant for public viewing. Despite that, anyone who visited us was totally wowed and mesmerized by it because it held so many colors..honestly it must have over 200. And so I always wanted to find a more polished way to share our color with our clients particularly when we would present in a trade show booth. Then lighting struck a few years ago when we built these shelves and put up this wall of peony vases. Now everyone likes to take their photo in front of it! Now@that I’m thinking about it..Do we need that? An entire WALL OF COLOR? You decide!

🔥BIG REVEAL🔥sort of. I started my business because I like to make things. But running a business can easily take you away from the parts of it that you love. So a couple of years back I decided to devote a few days a month to having fun just making stuff and playing around. I threw these little plates for my baby @istealpens_ 💗 who lives in NYC and loves my vintage work ( though she hated how mismatched it was when she was growing up with it..isn’t that the way?) So BOOM BOOM here are the 5th and 6th plates in a series of 8.

Peony Vases have the best functionality IMHO. There are no end of uses in the bed bath office garden or (duh) kitchen. But at my house spoons are how I use a peony vase. This one is in Hampton Links which is pretty vintage but I think you see my point. My mom @mimirosenwald taught me to keep the spoons out on the counter and it’s def a baller move.
